@NODE INUNP "UNPACKING"

This is very simple, just seven steps to Mosaic-heaven:

1> This is only a FAQ! Please RTFM!!!! for the full story.

2>  The  main binary 'Mosaic-AmiTCP'.  I've renamed this as 'mosaic' merely to
ease the typing in the Shell.  A probably safer way is to put an Alias in your
User-Startup file in s:  such as:

	Alias mosaic Mosaic-AmiTCP

I STRONGLY recommend you put it in AmiTCP:bin for two reasons:

	i)  You can then type 'mosaic' in the Shell to execute it.
	ii) I am in the process of modifying @{"Plink2.1" LINK ADP}so you can boot directly
into mosaic by typing 'plink up mosaic'.

3>  The  ENVARC:   directory.   Copy it's contents to your ENVARC:  directory,
usually in Workbench:prefs.  The Envarc:mosaic/prefs file WILL be @{"modified" LINK MPMOD} by
you at a latter date, but not just now.

4>  The REXX: directory. Copy it's contents to your s: directory.

5>  The  DOCS:   directory.   For  ease  of  use  I've put this in the AmiTCP:
directory so it's easy to get to later.

6>  As  a minimum I would suggest that you also install @{"ZGIF" LINK ADDT} again it is very
simple to install so RTFM :)

7>  That's  it you're all done now, all that remains is.....  Sit back, have a
cuppa and relax....  until...

@ENDNODE

