@NODE FTIME "THE FIRST TIME... for real!"

	We all remember the 1st time...  You're not quite sure what to expect,
but  you have a general idea of what to do, but no idea of where it will lead.
You  feel  both  nervous  but excited by all the hype you've heard.  So you've
done  your  best,  got all the bits together that you need and you work up the
courage and decide to go for it!

	You  turn  on  your Amiga and startup AmiTCP with 'link up' or, if you
have  phil's @{"plink" LINK ADP} utility, 'plink up nospeak nomailkick'.  Once you have got
your  shell  prompt type 'mosaic'<RET>.  The screen should swap to the AMosaic
screen  and  mosaic  will be displayed.  Size it to whatever you want (usually
the  full  screen).  There should be a 'flashing' button in the lower right of
the  window,  showing  that things are working.  It is actually making contact
with the Home Page @{"2.x" System "SYS:c/PPShow Amosaic.iff"}/@{"3.x" LINK Amosaic.iff/main}. This is your springboard into the world of Mosaic.

	Once  loaded  you  will be presented with the latest 'Home page', this
will tell you of the latest version of Mosaic (v1.2.1 more of this in the next
