@NODE TGIF "Transparent GIF's"

	What is it?
		It  is a picture format (GIF!) that allows a background colour
to be transparent.  Much like when you are in DPaint and hit b (for brush) and
cut  a section of the picture.  when you move that brush over you picture, you
can 'see through' the background colour.  For more info check out:

	http://dragon.jpl.nasa.gov/~adam/transparent.html
	http://sunsite.unc.edu/boutell/faq/www_faq.html#transparent

GifTool (from Home Pages, Inc.) has been ported to the Amiga by (I believe)
Jeff Thieleke. It supports transparent GIFs.

	http://ftp.wustl.edu/~aminet/dirs/aminet/gfx/misc/giftool.readme
	http://ftp.wustl.edu/~aminet/dirs/aminet/gfx/misc/giftool.lha

@ENDNODE

